The paper deals with optimization problems related to scheduling and resource allocation, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and control systems (cs.SY). The use of primal-dual algorithms and dynamic programming also suggests a connection to these subfields.
